<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 2:00AM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A LINE OF GUSTY SHOWERS WILL AFFECT SOUTHEASTERN
ROCKINGHAM...CASWELL...SOUTHEASTERN CHARLOTTE... SOUTHEASTERN
PITTSYLVANIA AND HALIFAX COUNTIES AND THE SOUTHEASTERN CITY OF
DANVILLE...
At 200 AM EST, radar indicated showers were located along a line
extending from near Ridgeway to near Monroeton. Movement was east at
30 mph.
Wind gusts up to 50 mph are possible with these showers.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Reidsville...
South Boston...
Yanceyville...
Bethel...
Halifax...
and Jericho.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
